This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel framework for Multitask Learning (MTL) using support vector machines. The paper also discusses the optimization of multiple objective functions, which is a common topic in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed framework is applied to classification tasks, which are often studied in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
